      "content": "i hear that, but i'm looking at it from a different angle. if this mostly just hits people who can't afford to live in the city or move to more remote areas, isn't that basically just a regressive tax on the working class? feels like the \"environmental benefit\" comes at the expense of people who are already struggling.",
