      "content": "You are hitting on the most critical ethical objection to congestion pricing, which is its potential for disproportionate financial impact on low-income essential workers. If implemented without robust mitigation strategies, it absolutely functions as a regressive tax, effectively penalizing those with the least flexibility. Therefore, for the policy to be considered equitable, the revenue must be explicitly earmarked to subsidize public transit fares or provide targeted financial relief to affected residents.",
